  "words": "Philip Doddridge, 1735",
  "music": "or &#39;Richmond (Haweis)&#39; or &#39;Spa Fields Chapel&#39; Thomas Haweis, 1792",
  "tune": "Chesterfield",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Hark, the glad sound! the Savior comes! The Savior promised long; Let every heart prepare a throne, And every voice a song.",
    "v2": "On Him the Spirit, largely poured, Exerts its sacred Fire; Wisdom and might, and zeal and love, His holy Breast inspire.",
    "v3": "He comes the pris&#39;ners to release, In Satan&#39;s bondage held; The gates of brass before Him burst, The iron fetters yield.",
    "v4": "He comes from thickest films of vice To clear the mental ray, And on the eyeballs of the blind To pour celestial day.",
    "v5": "He comes the broken heart to bind, The bleeding soul to cure; And with the treasures of His grace T&#39;enrich the humble poor."
  },
